x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Nuclear Science and Engineering, Vol.146, Issue.2, p.209 (2004)

x4freetext: Main reference, Graphs and
resonance parameters are given
Electron Lineal 46 Mev accelerator,
30 MeV electron beam energy. acting in two modes.
One - for neutron energy EN below 20 eV, pulse rate
50 Hz, pulse duration 3 microsec, peak electron
current 0.4 A. The other - for EN more than 2 eV,
pulse rate 200 Hz, pulse width 100 nanosec, peak
electron current 6 A.
.Flight path is 12.7+-0.02 m, electron beam
directed to 135 degree relative to flight path
.Pulse height discrimination
.Single target measurements
For neutron flux monitoring
Capture g-ray detector is BGO assembly as a
total energy absorption detector consisting of
12 scintillation bricks 5.0*5.0*7.5 cm each.
Total volume of BGO scintillators is 2.25 litres
For auxilary gamma-ray detection
Photoneutrons from electron bremsstrahlung
on tantalum target assembly, 5 cm in diameter, 6 cm
long, which was composed of 12 sheets of Ta plates
with total thickness 29 mm. This target was set at
the center of water - tank 30 cm in diameter, 35 cm
hight - serving as a neutron moderator.
.Neutron collimation system was composed of lead and
B4-C, H2-B-O3, Paraffin-Li2-C-O3 and lead bricks 5 to
10 cm thick
.Corrections were made for neutron multiple scattering
and self-absorption in sample with the help of Monte
Carlo calculations employing MCNP code, and for back-
ground of neutrons measured experimentally
.Tecnetium oxide Tc-O2 powder, weight 72.8 milligram
packed, 16 mm diameter, 1.1 mm thick, at the center
of aluminium disk container 30 mm diameter, 1.9 mm
thick. Thickness of the oxide sample is 0.145 gr/cm2.
Chemical purity of sample is more than 95%, content
of water less than 0.5% by weight.
.The disk container without the sample material has
been used for background measurements in the TOF
experiment
.Boron sample for the measurement of the neutron flux
was made of natural boron powder encapsulated in a
thin aluminium case, 18*18 mm and 5 mm thick, boron
thickness is 1.102 gram/cm2. Sample inserted into
the neutron beam instead of capture sample
- Total error equal to the quadratic sum
of its constituents
- Error due to deviation from 1/v form in
B-10(N,alpha) cross section
- Background subtraction error
- Max error due to correction for neutron
self-shielding and/or scattering effect
- Min error due to correction for neutron
self-shielding and/or scattering effect
- Normalisation error

Corrected SM
